\ choose ( list cont -- ): run cont with each element in turn; commit to the
\ first element for which cont succeeds, fail if none do.

\ commits to the first element greater than 3
[( 1 2 3 4 5 null )] [: |> x | x 3 gt if x . else fail then :] choose cr

\ a single-element list
[( 9 null )] [: |> x | x . :] choose cr

\ enumerate every element by printing and failing; an outer amb catches the final fail
[: [( 1 2 3 null )] [: |> x | x . fail :] choose :] [: 0 . :] amb cr

\ no element succeeds: the whole choose fails into the outer branch
[: [( 1 2 null )] [: drop fail :] choose :] [: 42 . :] amb cr

bye
